{
  "texts": [
    "They propose a framework called Private Evolution (PE), which uses evolutionary algorithms and models supported by existing APIs to generate synthetic data similar to the distribution of private data through an iterative process that ensures differential privacy protection.",
    "Ni et al. (2023) proposes a new method called Degeneration-Tuning (DT).",
    "The core idea of the method is to create a degraded dataset by disrupting low-frequency visual content and retuning the stable diffusion model to mask unwanted concepts when generating images, thus protecting certain concepts from attacks or leaks.",
    "The rapid development of image generation technology based on diffusion models has greatly enriched the opportunities for creative expression and visual content production, but it also raises serious copyright issues (Wang et al. 2024; Dubinski et al. 2024).",
    "These technologies can imitate or even create original works with high fidelity, making copyright ownership ambiguous and affecting the protection of rights for original creators (Gu et al. 2024; Zhang et al. 2023)."
  ]
}